  \cf4 16611. \cf6 15011-Root-Map.md\cf5  Starter\
  \cf4 16612. \cf6 # BlackRoad Universal Root Map\cf5 \
  \cf4 16613. \cf6 Purpose: define the 15000-series address space as the local universal map for orgs, repos, files, agents,\cf5 \
     \cf6 atoms, proof, merge, promotion, archive, and control.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16614. \cf6 Root: /Applications/BlackRoad-Portable/15000-BlackRoad-Universal\cf5 \
  \cf4 16615. \cf6 Primary Layers: 15100 ORGS | 15200 REPOS | 15300 FILES | 15400 AGENTS | 15500 ATOMS | 15600 PROOF | 15700\cf5 \
     \cf6 MERGE | 15800 PROMOTION | 15900 ARCHIVE\cf5 \
  \cf4 16616. \cf6 Canonical Rule: this tree is addressable, portable, and crosswalk-friendly.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16617. \cf6 Review Status: Draft\cf5 \
  \cf4 16618. \cf6 Owner: Roadie\cf5 \
  \cf4 16619. \cf6 Last Review: 2026-04-09\cf5 \
  \cf4 16620. \cf5 Root Map Index\
  \cf4 16621. \cf6 15012-Address-Space-Rules.md\cf5  Starter\
  \cf4 16622. \cf6 # Address Space Rules\cf5 \
  \cf4 16623. \cf6 Every org, repo, file, agent, and change atom gets a stable numeric anchor.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16624. \cf6 Numeric anchors must not be silently reused.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16625. \cf6 Old names survive through crosswalks, aliases, and supersession registers.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16626. \cf6 Human-readable labels should sit beside numeric anchors.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16627. \cf6 The system must support local-first work, Gitea canonicality, and public mirrors as downstream copies\cf5 \
     \cf6 only.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16628. \cf6 Unknown values must be marked Pending.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16629. \cf6 All promotions must remain reversible.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16630. \cf5 Address Space Rules Index\
