  \cf4 16661. \cf6 15016-Change-Atom-Rules.md\cf5  Starter\
  \cf4 16662. \cf6 # Change Atom Rules\cf5 \
  \cf4 16663. \cf6 One atom = one atomic contribution.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16664. \cf6 Every atom must have intent, target, proof path, and current state.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16665. \cf6 Atoms should be promotable independently.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16666. \cf6 Atoms should be rollback-safe independently.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16667. \cf6 Atoms should link upward to goals and tasks.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16668. \cf6 Atoms should not rely on branch names alone for identity.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16669. \cf6 Atoms must remain addressable in the 15500 layer.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16670. \cf5 Change Atom Rules Index\
  \cf4 16671. \cf6 15017-Proof-Rules.md\cf5  Starter\
  \cf4 16672. \cf6 # Proof Rules\cf5 \
  \cf4 16673. \cf6 Every promoted contribution needs proof.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16674. \cf6 Proof types include text, file, diff, screenshot, log, test, review, and external source.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16675. \cf6 Proof must map to a claim or atom.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16676. \cf6 Proof must carry source, date, and reviewer or validator where possible.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16677. \cf6 Proof should be both human-readable and machine-indexable.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16678. \cf6 Proof should survive rollback and supersession.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16679. \cf6 Proof lives in the 15600 layer.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16680. \cf5 Proof Rules Index\
  \cf4 16681. \cf6 15018-Promotion-Rules.md\cf5  Starter\
  \cf4 16682. \cf6 # Promotion Rules\cf5 \
  \cf4 16683. \cf6 Nothing becomes canonical silently.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16684. \cf6 Promotion requires passing gates for intent, proof, dependencies, contradictions, and review.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16685. \cf6 Mirrors are downstream of canonicals.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16686. \cf6 Superseded canonicals remain traceable.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16687. \cf6 Rollback is first-class.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16688. \cf6 Promotion state must be queryable across the local portable system.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16689. \cf6 Promotion lives in the 15800 layer.\cf5 \
  \cf4 16690. \cf5 Promotion Rules Index\
